\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs32 \cf2 This is the other way APNs allows us to send notifications. In this case we don't need a certificate but we will need a\'a0
\f3\fs27\fsmilli13600 \cb6 p8
\f0\fs32 \cb3 \'a0file with the private key we will use to sign the token. Lets assume we've got the file\'a0
